description.narrative: By 2023, national and sub-national administrations have strengthened capacity to formulate policies and plans to address multi- dimensional child poverty, with sound M&E systems., which contributes to Adolescent Empowerment, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance, Children In Urban Settings / Local Governance (Covid), Children With Disabilities, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Evaluation And Research, Evaluation And Research (Covid), Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, children and adolescents, including the most disadvantaged, benefit from effective social services and a child-sensitive social protection system.

description.narrative: The sub-national planning and budgeting advocacy for social services for children in support of the integrated early childhood development has been expanded to 25 provinces, moving from previously seven targeted provinces. Two key strategic interventions were rolled out to strengthen capacity of Ministry of Interior in monitoring and evaluation and governance of sub-national administration (SNA), the sub-national planning and budgeting online database and reward recognition mechanism. The sub-national project and budget database is being developed with the view of linking the SNA planning and budget functions into a consolidated monitoring mechanism informing the performance assessment and budget advocacy | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
